article.description: Andrea Riley scored a season-low 14 points but Oklahoma State avoided an upset by defeating in-state rival Oral Roberts 58-48.
article.headline: Oklahoma State holds off Oral Roberts
article.linkText: Oklahoma State avoids Oral Roberts upset bid
article.story:
STILLWATER, Okla. -- Andrea Riley scored a season-low 14 points but Oklahoma State (No. 23 ESPN/USA Today, No. 22 AP) avoided an upset by defeating in-state rival Oral Roberts 58-48 on Tuesday.

Riley entered the game ranked ninth nationally in scoring at 21.5 points per game but went 2-of-14 from the field, including 1-of-8 from 3-point range, and committed eight turnovers. She went 9-of-14 from the free-throw line.

Tegan Cunningham led Oklahoma State (5-2) with 16 points.

Oral Roberts (5-5) has lost four straight games. Janae Voelker led the Golden Eagles with 14 points, with Mariana Camargo and Georgia Jones adding 12 each.

Oklahoma State has won 28 consecutive home games against nonconference opponents.
